<h1 class="sectionedit1"><a name="general" id="general">General:</a></h1>
<div class="level1">

<p>
Weapon files should be named .wpn and placed under the <code>gusanos/mod/weapons/</code> directory.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT1 SECTION "General:" [1-116] -->
<h1 class="sectionedit2"><a name="properties" id="properties">Properties:</a></h1>
<div class="level1">

<p>
Weapon properties must be added to the .wpn file before events. These properties may only be used in .wpn files.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT2 SECTION "Properties:" [117-258] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit3"><a name="ammo" id="ammo">ammo</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">ammo = &lt;int&gt;</pre>

<p>
Determines how much ammo the weapon holds.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Default value:</strong> 1
</p>

<p>
Also use <strong>use_ammo</strong> to drain ammo from weapons from now on.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT3 SECTION "ammo" [259-421] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit4"><a name="laser_sight_alpha" id="laser_sight_alpha">laser_sight_alpha</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">laser_sight_alpha = &lt;int&gt; ( from 0 to 255 )</pre>

<p>
Determines the translucency of the lasersight. It only works if <strong>laser_sight_blender</strong> is not equal to “none”.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Default value:</strong> 255
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT4 SECTION "laser_sight_alpha" [422-635] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit5"><a name="laser_sight_blender" id="laser_sight_blender">laser_sight_blender</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">laser_sight_blender = { add, alpha, none }</pre>

<p>
Determines the blender with which the laser sight will be drawn.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Default value:</strong> none
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT5 SECTION "laser_sight_blender" [636-805] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit6"><a name="laser_sight_color_laser_sight_colour" id="laser_sight_color_laser_sight_colour">laser_sight_color / laser_sight_colour</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">laser_sight_colour = [ &lt;int&gt; r, &lt;int&gt; g, &lt;int&gt; b ] ( All ranging from 0 to 255 )</pre>
<pre class="code">e.g.
laser_sight_colour = [ 255, 128, 0] # Makes an orange laser sight</pre>

<p>
Determines the colour ( in RGB format ) with which the laser sight will be drawn.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Default value:</strong> [ 255, 0, 0 ]
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT6 SECTION "laser_sight_color / laser_sight_colour" [806-1134] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit7"><a name="laser_sight_intensity" id="laser_sight_intensity">laser_sight_intensity</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">laser_sight_intensity = &lt;float&gt; ( from 0 to 1 )</pre>

<p>
Its the intensity of the laser sight of the weapon. 1 is full intensity, 0.5 half, 0 no laser sight.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Default value:</strong> 0
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT7 SECTION "laser_sight_intensity" [1135-1343] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit8"><a name="laser_sight_range" id="laser_sight_range">laser_sight_range</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">laser_sight_range = &lt;float&gt;</pre>

<p>
Is the distance in which the lasersight will fade completely from the given laser_sight_intensity to 0 intensity. -1 will make it not fade.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Default value:</strong> -1
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT8 SECTION "laser_sight_range" [1344-1568] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit9"><a name="name" id="name">name</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">name = &lt;string&gt;</pre>

<p>
The name of the weapon.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Default value:</strong> ””
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT9 SECTION "name" [1569-1652] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit10"><a name="reload_time" id="reload_time">reload_time</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">reload_time = &lt;int&gt;</pre>

<p>
Determines the time in frames that will take for the weapon to reload.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Default value:</strong> 0
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT10 SECTION "reload_time" [1653-1793] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit11"><a name="skin" id="skin">skin</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">skin = &lt;string&gt;</pre>

<p>
The image that will be displayed on top of the worm.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Default value:</strong> null
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT11 SECTION "skin" [1794-1908] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit12"><a name="sync_reload" id="sync_reload">sync_reload</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">sync_reload = &lt;bool&gt;</pre>

</div>
<!-- EDIT12 SECTION "sync_reload" [1909-1956] -->
<h1 class="sectionedit13"><a name="events" id="events">Events:</a></h1>
<div class="level1">

</div>
<!-- EDIT13 SECTION "Events:" [1957-1981] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit14"><a name="active_timer" id="active_timer">active_timer</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">on active_timer( &lt;int&gt; delay, &lt;int&gt; delay_var = 0, &lt;int&gt; max_trigger = 0 , &lt;int&gt; start_delay = 0 )</pre>

<p>
It behaves the same as a normal timer except that it will only count time when the weapon is selected and it gets reset when the player changes to another weapon. <strong>start_delay</strong> is how much time it should wait to start counting time, if set to -1 the time will be equal to the delay + variation.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Example:</strong>
</p>
<pre class="code">on active_timer( 0, max_trigger = 1 )
play_sound( sword_chosen.wav )</pre>

<p>
This would play the sound sword_chosen.wav every time the player changes to the sword (this) weapon.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT14 SECTION "active_timer" [1982-2595] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit15"><a name="primary_shoot" id="primary_shoot">primary_shoot</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">on primary_shoot()</pre>

<p>
It will trigger while the gun is shooting.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT15 SECTION "primary_shoot" [2596-2687] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit16"><a name="primary_press" id="primary_press">primary_press</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">on primary_press()</pre>

<p>
It will trigger <strong>once</strong> when the player presses the fire button.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT16 SECTION "primary_press" [2688-2802] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit17"><a name="primary_release" id="primary_release">primary_release</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">on primary_release()</pre>

<p>
It will trigger <strong>once</strong> when the player releases the fire button.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT17 SECTION "primary_release" [2803-2922] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit18"><a name="out_of_ammo" id="out_of_ammo">out_of_ammo</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">on out_of_ammo()</pre>

<p>
It will trigger <strong>once</strong> when the weapon gets out of ammo.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT18 SECTION "out_of_ammo" [2923-3026] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit19"><a name="reload_end" id="reload_end">reload_end</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">on reload_end()</pre>

<p>
It will trigger <strong>once</strong> when the weapon reloading ends.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT19 SECTION "reload_end" [3027-3126] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit20"><a name="timer" id="timer">timer</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="code">on timer ( &lt;int&gt; delay, &lt;int&gt; delay_var = 0, &lt;int&gt; trigger_times = 0 )</pre>

<p>
The timer will get triggered every <strong>delay</strong> frames plus the <strong>delay_var</strong>. If the <strong>trigger_times</strong> param is bigger than 0 then the timer will only be triggered that amount of times.
</p>

</div>
